      "tree": {
        "sha": "d8290517db6518b34425dd8d65105f479d7d5ba1",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/d8290517db6518b34425dd8d65105f479d7d5ba1"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree d8290517db6518b34425dd8d65105f479d7d5ba1\nparent ad0545ba967b110f95a2ef22959b78128f8409ea\nauthor Thomas <thomas.giudici@proton.me> 1776686230 +0200\ncommitter Thomas <thomas.giudici@proton.me> 1776686230 +0200\n\nbtcsignals: disconnect old connection on scoped_connection move-assignment\n\nThe defaulted move-assignment operator for scoped_connection overwrites\nm_conn without first disconnecting the previously held connection. This\ncauses the old callback to remain registered in the signal and continue\nfiring indefinitely -- violating the RAII contract of scoped_connection.\n\nReplace the defaulted operator with a custom one that calls disconnect()\nbefore moving, and add a regression test that covers both the normal case\nand self-move-assignment.\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN SSH SIGNATURE-----\nU1NIU0lHAAAAAQAAADMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAAAgla6CTpRESyZie3IYSH62eCKYaN\nVPdtIneEm9EzHImo4AAAADZ2l0AAAAAAAAAAZzaGE1MTIAAABTAAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5\nAAAAQOS5wcYJSfYieLARsh38aFsMdJAjbIu4h6XRYe8FWY//3tBKsb2+u9DmDAztb0WfVi\nMp7wlkIpNw/854YN0WGQc=\n-----END SSH SIGNATURE-----"
      },
